         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>Line 1, the double nomen suggests a name soon after the Edict of Caracalla; the cognomen really does not seem to be Βετ<unclear>ρ</unclear>α-
            </p>
            <p>Line 2: the text would seem to be in verse: for the not uncommon attribution of death to a decision of fate, and for the introduction of a δαίμων rather than Μοῖρα or Hades, 
               see Lattimore, <title><ref target="https://zenon.dainst.org/Record/001350019">Themes in Greek and Latin epitaphs</ref></title>, p. 148.</p>
         </div>
         
